'''Force Stasis''' was a [[Telekinesis|telekinetic]] [[Force power]] used to restrain and immobilize people or objects.

==Description==
Force Stasis<ref name="Destiny">{{Destiny|set=Star Wars: Destiny Two-Player Game|cardname=Force Stasis|link=https://swdestinydb.com/card/04008}}</ref> was an [[Force power|ability]] of [[the Force]] to [[Telekinesis|forcibly]] restrain and immobilize people or to halt objects headed in a [[Force-sensitive|Force-user's]] direction. The ability allowed its users to cancel out the motion of a target, not only reducing its speed but even suspending it in place. The effect could at times be temporary, allowing the target to regain its motion, but could also be so powerful that, unlike normal applications of telekinesis, continuous conscious effort and physical gestures were not always necessary to maintain it. Additionally, the most skilled or powerful users could even exert this paralyzing grip on non-material objects, such as blaster bolts.<ref name="Episode VII" />

==History==
===Republic Era===
[[File:Mission_to_Rugosa3.png|thumb|left|250px|Master Yoda holds back Asajj Ventress's strike against King Katuunko.]]
During the [[Night of Sorrow]]<ref name="Vengence">''[[The High Republic: Path of Vengeance]]''</ref> in [[382 BBY]],<ref name="Timelines">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]''</ref> the [[Wookiee]] [[Jukkyuk]], a [[bodyguard]] for [[Mother (title)|Mother]] [[Elecia Zeveron]], was stirred into a frenzy by [[Guide of the Closed Fist|Guide]] [[Marda Ro]], who convinced the Wookiee to battle with the [[Jedi Order]] so she could get through to Zeveron. Rushing through the tunnels, Jukkyuk soon encountered and fired upon three Jedi, [[Padawan]] [[Matthea Cathley]], [[Jedi Knight]] [[Azlin Rell]], and fellow Knight [[Oliviah Zeveron]]. Zeveron responded to the attack with an act of Force Stasis: with a simple raise of her hand, Zeveron stopped the incoming blaster bolt in its tracks and then pushed it back towards Jukkyuk, who fell to his own blast but survived.<ref name="Vengence" />

[[Twin]] sisters [[Verosha Aniseya|Verosha]] and [[Mae-ho Aniseya]] used Force Stasis on a [[Brendoki flutterby]] on the [[planet]] [[Brendok]]<ref name="DestinyAcolyte">{{Acolyte|Destiny (The Acolyte)}}</ref> in [[148 BBY]].<ref name="DestinyTimeline">{{TheAcolyteDate}} "[[Destiny (The Acolyte)|Destiny]]" establishes the events of the episode to take place 16 years earlier, placing the events of the episode to [[148 BBY]].</ref> [[Yoda]] used the power to freeze [[Asajj Ventress]] in place as she tried to [[Death|kill]] [[King]] [[Katuunko]]<ref name="Ambush" /> in [[22 BBY]].<ref name="Timelines" />

===Imperial Era===
[[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] used this ability, while attacking the [[Jedi outpost]] ''[[Brighthome]]'', to momentarily contain and slow down the process of a [[grenade]] exploding long enough for him to get away from it.<ref name="Dark Lord 2">[[Darth Vader (2017) 2|''Darth Vader'' (2017) 2]]</ref>

Jedi [[Padawan]] [[Cal Kestis]], who was proficient with Force Stasis, used it to slow the movements of a group of [[clone trooper]]s after they fatally wounded his master [[Jaro Tapal]] during the activation of [[Order 66]]. Five years later, Cal used Force Stasis to suspend the [[Scrapper Guild]] worker [[Prauf]] in mid-air, saving him from a fatal fall. In his subsequent [[Secret mission to rebuild the Jedi Order|mission to rebuild the Jedi Order]], Kestis used Stasis to traverse landscapes by temporarily slowing down fast-moving platforms. He also used it in battle to slow the movements of his opponents and to slow enemy [[blaster]] [[Laser|shots]].<ref name="Jedi: Fallen Order">''[[Star Wars Jedi: Fallen Order]]''</ref> When Kestis used this ability in conjunction with the [[dark side of the Force]], him attacks could be more dangerous, as Force Stasis further reduced him enemies' reaction speed and increased the range to affect more opponents. Overcome by immense anger that nearly caused him to lose himself, he used this ability to leave a [[Mission to Nova Garon|trail of destruction and death]] on the [[II-0810 Satellite Station]], claiming the lives of several members of the [[Inquisitorius]] and the [[Imperial Security Bureau]].<ref>[[Star Wars Jedi: Survivor]]</ref>

[[File:BarrissStopsLightsaber-TWO.png|thumb|right|250px|The Fourth Sister's attack is thwarted.]]
Jedi [[Barriss Offee]] used Force Stasis against the [[Inquisitor]] [[Fourth Sister]], buying time for a family to escape with their baby, who was a target of the Inquisitor due to its [[Force-sensitive|Force sensitivity]].<ref>[[Star Wars: Tales of the Underworld]] — "[[The Way Out]]"</ref>

===New Republic/First Order Era===
[[File:EzraStopsShinLightsaber-Ahsoka.png|thumb|left|250px|Ezra Bridger uses Force Stasis during his fight with Shin Hati.]]
Around [[9 ABY]], the [[Bokken Jedi]] [[Ezra Bridger]] would use this ability to freeze a [[Shin Hati's lightsaber|lightsaber]] strike from the [[mercenary]] [[Shin Hati]] during their brief fight on [[Peridea]].<ref name="Part Seven">{{Ahsoka|Part Seven: Dreams and Madness}}</ref>

During the [[attack on Tuanul]], [[Ben Solo|Kylo Ren]] utilized this ability to hold off a blaster bolt headed in his direction (while simultaneously freezing the person holding the blaster, [[Poe Dameron]], in place) long enough for his [[First Order stormtrooper|stormtroopers]] to bring his would-be killer to talk to him, and then released it after aiming it out of the way and retreating from the area full of people. Later, during the [[Battle of Takodana]], Ren utilized this ability to capture [[Rey Skywalker|Rey]], shortly before forcing her to fall [[Sleep|unconscious]].<ref name="Episode VII" />

[[File:ReyBlocksSaber-TROS.png|thumb|right|250px|Rey uses Force Stasis to block Kylo Ren's lightsaber strike.]]
In [[35 ABY]], during the [[Mission to Kef Bir]], Rey and Kylo Ren had a duel on the [[Death Star ruins|ruins]] of the [[DS-2 Death Star II Mobile Battle Station|second Death Star]]. During the fight, both of them used Force Stasis to block each other's lightsaber strikes, with each combatant holding back the other's blade before it could make contact with them. Later, during the [[Battle of Exegol]], the barely alive [[Darth Sidious]] used this ability to subdue Rey and the redeemed Ben Solo, leaving them powerless as he [[Force drain|drained]] the [[Force dyad|Dyad's]] life force to rejuvenate and restore himself to his former strength, comparable to his at the [[time]] of his [[Duel in Palpatine's office|triumph]] on [[Coruscant]] and his [[Battle of Endor|defeat]] over [[Endor]].<ref name="Episode IX">{{Film|IX}}</ref>

